Graptoveria are hybrid crosses between Graptopetalum and Echeveria. A diverse genus, most are low growing, cultivated for their beautiful shapes and colours.Plants are well rooted, includes pot, soil and label with common and botanical names and planting directions. Plants in 2.5" pots range in size from 2.5 to 3.5 inches. Plants in 3.5 inch post range in size from 3" to 5". Create your own container garden or centerpiece using  these very popular succulents, or buy in bulk to use as wedding or party favors.

CULTIVATION TIPS
Graptoveria are hardy plants requiring porous soil with excellent drainange. Water regularly over the summer months letting the soil dry out between waterings. Minimal water is required over winter. Fertilize once during the growing season with a balanced fertilizer diluted to ¼ strength. All do best in sun or part sun.
